#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:1
msgid "vtkDelimitedTextReader improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:3
msgid "Preview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:5
msgid ""
"vtkDelimitedTextReader offers a `GetPreview` method to inspect the file "
"content. During the `RequestInformation` pass, it reads the "
"`PreviewNumberOfLines` first lines of the input file. By default, nothing is "
"done and Preview is empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:10
msgid ""
"This is useful to configure the reader options (like `XXXDelimiters` or "
"`HaveHeaders`) before the `RequestData` pass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:13
msgid "SkippedRecords"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:15
msgid ""
"The new `SkippedRecords` option allows to skip the first N records (usually "
"lines). This is useful as some file format may contain non standard header "
"lines. See for instance the [gslib](http://www.gslib.com/gslib_help/format."
"html) format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:19
msgid "Comments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/delimited-text-reader-options.md:21
msgid ""
"vtkDelimitedTextReader supports the concept of comments: starting at on of "
"the given `CommentCharacters`, the remaining data of the current record is "
"skipped."
msgstr ""
